Git Essentials: CH_6 Use Git with a Real Project.

CH 6: The Explore California Website

  - View Commit: Review previous commits

    - Edit explore_california: index.html
      - you'll to you will

    - cmd: "git diff --color-words" which zeros in on the exact change and leaves out the rest of the text not changed.

    - What if you want to review a previous commit?

      - cmd: "git show and the <SHA val, first 7 digits>"
        - e.g. cmd: "git show 1c16945"
        - this enough information for git to identify the specific commit 6 - 8 char. for the size of the example project/commits.
        - and or cmd: "git show 1c16945 --color-words" - just changes

      
